ARTHUR SWANN v. STATE OF MARYLAND. Decided July 8th, 1927.

The cause was argued before Bond, O. J., Pattison, Adkins, Okfutt, Pabke, and Sloan, JJ.

Milton Dashiell, with whom was George L. Fornoff on the Jarief, for the appellant. John Huhner Rice, Assistant Attorney General, with whom were Thomas H. Robinson, Attorney General, and Ferdinand C. Cooksey, State’s Attorney for Charles County, on the brief, for the State. Bond, C. J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
